Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the *Full Stack Software Engineer* role with *Windfall*. I bring over three years of professional experience building and maintaining full-stack web applications, connecting services, and developing AI-driven features, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade backend systems that directly reflect *the full-stack technical depth and API-driven focus this position demands*. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected a full-stack AI interaction layer that translates natural-language intents into validated tool calls across 1,000+ platform endpoints — a project that required connecting multiple services and creating robust APIs to bring AI-driven features to life for internal teams. To keep these systems production-ready in a fast-paced environment, I implemented a full observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith, which reduced end-to-end latency by 60% and provided the high-leverage technical improvements the business relies on. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to the backbone infrastructure that internal teams depend on. I designed and developed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Java, Spring Boot, and PostgreSQL that seamlessly handled file operations across AWS S3 and Google Cloud Storage — giving me direct, hands-on experience with the GCP stack and transactional database management Windfall utilizes. I also developed a full-stack Identity & Access Management platform UI using React and Google Cloud, supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications, which required *the kind of rapid prototyping and end-to-end ownership this role demands*. Together, these roles have prepared me to *contribute meaningfully to the Application Team’s mission of building innovative, AI-driven features and complex tooling for internal teams*.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in model development and technical communication — skills that translate directly into *the technical integrity and collaborative engineering culture Windfall values*. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on generative models using PyTorch on high-performance clusters, ensuring impeccable attention to detail in system performance and secure deployment. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on building AI Agents with LangChain for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to be an excellent communicator, breaking down complex technical concepts clearly — directly mirroring *the collaborative spirit and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to working with senior leadership at Windfall*. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to *the Windfall team and its mission*.


I have always been passionate about *providing leverage, not optimization, and operating with absolute transparency* and envision myself contributing my talent to the furthering of *Windfall's mission to democratize access, workflows, and insights on people*. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

